---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Now City Labs" description="Development intelligence for what gets built next. Pre-development tools, systems methodology, and capital structuring for mission-aligned landowners, operators, and municipalities.">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="pt-20 pb-24 md:pt-28 md:pb-32">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <div class="eyebrow mb-6">Regenerative development intelligence</div>
        <h1 class="text-display-xl font-display text-forest-700">
          Development intelligence for what gets built next.
        </h1>
        <p class="lede mt-8 max-w-2xl text-stone-700">
          Now City Labs helps landowners, operators, and cities move from
          feasibility to funded — faster, with less risk and stronger long-term
          value.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-10 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row">
          <a href="/services/" class="btn-primary">See how we work</a>
          <a href="/outcomes/" class="btn-outline">Compare outcomes</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What we do / for whom -->
  <section class="border-y border-forest-700/10 bg-cream-50 py-20">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="grid gap-12 md:grid-cols-12">
        <div class="md:col-span-4">
          <div class="eyebrow mb-4">Who we serve</div>
          <h2 class="text-display-md font-display text-forest-700">
            Built for the people who actually move projects forward.
          </h2>
        </div>
        <div class="md:col-span-8">
          <div class="grid gap-10 sm:grid-cols-2">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-forest-700">Landowners</h3>
              <p class="prose-body mt-3">
                Sites large enough to become neighborhoods — family holdings,
                institutional campuses, waterfront reuse, multi-parcel
                assemblages. You have the land. We provide the pathway.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-forest-700">Operators & developers</h3>
              <p class="prose-body mt-3">
                Regional teams who want better capital terms, tighter
                pre-development, and a differentiated product in
                competitive markets.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-forest-700">Municipalities</h3>
              <p class="prose-body mt-3">
                Cities and agencies focused on housing production,
                community outcomes, and delivery partners they can trust.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-forest-700">Mission-aligned capital</h3>
              <p class="prose-body mt-3">
                Impact funds, CDFIs, and institutional LPs looking for
                credible operators, measurable outcomes, and durable
                real-asset portfolios.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Outcomes snapshot -->
  <section class="py-24">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="mb-12 max-w-2xl">
        <div class="eyebrow mb-4">Why it matters</div>
        <h2 class="text-display-md font-display text-forest-700">
          Better projects. Better capital. Better outcomes.
        </h2>
        <p class="prose-body mt-6">
          The traditional development process is itself the source of risk,
          cost, and delay. Pro-formas drive the plan. Utilities get sized
          late. Community engagement arrives after decisions are made.
          Identity gets value-engineered out. We flip the order — land and
          systems determine the plan.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-forest-700/10 bg-cream-50 p-8">
          <div class="font-display text-4xl text-forest-700">6–18 mo</div>
          <div class="eyebrow mt-2">Faster to shovel-ready</div>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-stone-600">
            Systems-aligned pre-development reduces redesign, rework, and
            late-stage entitlement battles.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-forest-700/10 bg-cream-50 p-8">
          <div class="font-display text-4xl text-forest-700">15–30%</div>
          <div class="eyebrow mt-2">Lower infrastructure cap-ex</div>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-stone-600">
            Integrated energy, water, and mobility analysis right-sizes
            systems before design begins.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-forest-700/10 bg-cream-50 p-8">
          <div class="font-display text-4xl text-forest-700">Durable</div>
          <div class="eyebrow mt-2">Long-term asset value</div>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-stone-600">
            Identity, resilience, and operating performance compound
            over decades — not depreciate.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10">
        <a href="/outcomes/" class="text-forest-700 underline decoration-copper-400 decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-copper-400">
          Explore the full outcomes comparison →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Stack preview -->
  <section class="bg-forest-700 py-24 text-cream">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="grid gap-12 md:grid-cols-12">
        <div class="md:col-span-5">
          <div class="eyebrow mb-4 text-copper-200">The Now City Stack</div>
          <h2 class="text-display-md font-display text-cream">
            The stack behind regenerative development.
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-cream/85">
            Four integrated layers of capability — applied to the challenge
            of getting the right projects built.
          </p>
          <a href="/stack/" class="mt-8 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-cream underline decoration-copper-400 decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-copper-200">
            Explore the Stack →
          </a>
        </div>
        <div class="md:col-span-7">
          <dl class="space-y-8">
            <div class="border-t border-cream/20 pt-6">
              <dt class="font-display text-xl text-cream">Industrialized construction</dt>
              <dd class="mt-2 text-cream/75">
                Off-site, kit-of-parts assembly that compresses schedule,
                reduces waste, and improves build quality.
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div class="border-t border-cream/20 pt-6">
              <dt class="font-display text-xl text-cream">Green infrastructure</dt>
              <dd class="mt-2 text-cream/75">
                Energy, water, and mobility systems sized to the land, not
                the pro-forma. Lower cap-ex, lower op-ex, higher resilience.
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div class="border-t border-cream/20 pt-6">
              <dt class="font-display text-xl text-cream">Regenerative placemaking</dt>
              <dd class="mt-2 text-cream/75">
                Program, public realm, and ground-floor economics designed
                together. Identity emerges through systems, not signage.
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div class="border-t border-cream/20 pt-6">
              <dt class="font-display text-xl text-cream">Innovative finance</dt>
              <dd class="mt-2 text-cream/75">
                Public tools, philanthropy, private equity, and long-term
                debt structured into aligned capital stacks.
              </dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Platform strip -->
  <section class="border-y border-forest-700/10 bg-cream-50 py-16">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="grid gap-10 md:grid-cols-12 md:items-start">
        <div class="md:col-span-4">
          <div class="eyebrow mb-3">Part of Now City Inc.</div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-2xl leading-tight text-forest-700">
            Same world. Different door.
          </h2>
        </div>
        <div class="md:col-span-8 space-y-6">
          <p class="prose-body">
            Now City Labs is the development services and intelligence arm of Now City Inc. — alongside
            <a href="https://nowcity.co" rel="noopener" class="text-forest-700 underline decoration-copper-400 decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-copper-400">nowcity.co</a>
            for the neighborhood vision and lived experience, and
            <a href="https://urbanreboot.org" rel="noopener" class="text-forest-700 underline decoration-copper-400 decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-copper-400">Urban Reboot</a>
            for mission-aligned feasibility work.
          </p>
          <p class="prose-body text-stone-600">
            One platform, three doors — each pitched to a different audience. Where nowcity.co speaks
            to residents and neighborhood vision, nowcitylabs.com speaks to capability, rigor, and ROI.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Closing CTA -->
  <section class="py-24">
    <div class="container-narrow text-center">
      <h2 class="text-display-lg font-display text-forest-700">
        From feasibility to funded — faster.
      </h2>
      <p class="prose-body mx-auto mt-6 max-w-xl">
        We only take on a select number of engagements each quarter. If you
        have the land and a real question about what's possible, we should
        talk.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-10 flex flex-col items-center gap-3 sm:flex-row sm:justify-center">
        <a href="/services/#contact" class="btn-primary">Schedule a gateway call</a>
        <a href="/services/" class="btn-outline">See engagement framework</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
